$$ {\text{LVSWI}} = 0.0136 \cdot {\left( {{\text{MAP}} - {\text{PAOP}}} \right)} \cdot {\text{SV}}/{\text{BSA}} $$\end{document}the constant 0.0136 converts the units mmHg l/m2 to gm/m2. BSA (m2) is the body surface area given by the DuBois formula (Wang et al. 1992): 2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
